    <h1>02 - Tidy And Robotidy</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <div style=3D"display: none;">
<br>
</div>
<p>There are two methods to running tidy. This will update your .resource o=
r .robot file to match the community accepted Robot Framework style.</p>
<h2 id=3D"id-02TidyAndRobotidy-Tidy">Tidy</h2>
<p><a href=3D"https://robotframework.org/robotframework/latest/RobotFramewo=
rkUserGuide.html#tidy" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://rob=
otframework.org/robotframework/latest/RobotFrameworkUserGuide.html#tidy</a>=
</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">python =
-m robot.tidy -i -s 2 &lt;file_location&gt;</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>All files should have tidy executed on them.</p>
<p>'inplace' changes are recommended</p>
<p>2 spaces over the default 4 spaces to tighten up the code.</p>
<p>Pay attention to any formatting that was changed, especially if you 'tuc=
ked under' Lists and Dictionaries</p>
<p><u><strong>Run this tool before Robocop.</strong></u></p>
<h2 id=3D"id-02TidyAndRobotidy-Robotidy">Robotidy</h2>
<p>As of RF 4.x use of Robotidy is recommended.</p>
<p><a href=3D"https://github.com/MarketSquare/robotframework-tidy" class=3D=
"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://github.com/MarketSquare/robotframe=
work-tidy</a></p>
<p>Provides more control over resource/robot file style</p>
<p><u><strong>Run this tool before Robocop.</strong></u></p>
<p>A good thing to create for a project is a pyproject.toml file with all t=
he robotidy options set:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;">
<b>pyproject.toml</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence"># robot=
idy --spacecount 2 &lt;file.resource,file.robot,folder&gt;

[tool.robotidy]
overwrite =3D true
diff =3D true
configure =3D [
    "AlignSettingsSection: up_to_column=3D2",
    "AlignVariablesSection: up_to_column=3D3",
    "DiscardEmptySections: allow_only_comments=3DTrue",
    "NormalizeAssignments: equal_sign_type=3Dremove",
    "NormalizeNewLines: section_lines=3D2",
    "NormalizeNewLines: test_case_lines=3D1",
    "NormalizeNewLines: keyword_lines=3D1",
    "NormalizeNewLines: consecutive_lines=3D0",
    "NormalizeNewLines: separate_templated_tests=3DTrue",
    "NormalizeSectionHeaderName: uppercase=3Dfalse",
    "NormalizeSeparators",
    "NormalizeSettingName",
    "OrderSettingsSection:group_order=3Ddocumentation,imports,tags,settings=
",
    "ReplaceRunKeywordIf",
    "SplitTooLongLine: split_on_every_arg=3Dfalse",
    "SplitTooLongLine: line_length=3D120"
]

</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
